25.body: Currently two types of events are supported: buffered and immediate . Buffered events are dispatched at a specific time and place, whereas immediate are dispatched right after broadcasting.
25.title: Event types

26.body:
Mandatory functions Broadcast Used for firing events. template <typename Message>
void Broadcast(const Message& _message); AnyEvents Check if any events are remaining. bool AnyEvents() const; GetMessage Returns true if remaining event type is the same as Message type. template <typename Message>
bool GetMessage(Message* _pMessage); EventHandled Use if event was handled successfully. The event will be popped. template <typename Message>
void EventHandled(); Keep the event to the next frame. template <typename Message>
void EventHandled(const Message& _message); Reset void Reset(); Clear void Clear(); Skip void Skip();
26.title: Buffered events
